Cara-Lee Dorfling, Netwerk24(File, iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Port Elizabeth &ndash; A nine-year-old Jeffreys Bay girl died after her mother allegedly put sleeping pills into her milkshake,&nbsp;Netwerk24&nbsp;reported.&nbsp; After the girl&rsquo;s mother had a fall out with her friend, she put the pills into her daughter&rsquo;s milkshake before putting the girl to bed, and then consumed the pills herself.&ldquo;The mom woke up the next morning, but the daughter did not,&rdquo; police spokesperson Captain Gerda Swart told Netwerk24.&nbsp;When the mother realised on Thursday morning that her daughter had died, she allegedly tried to take her own life by slitting her wrists.A friend of the mother arrived and took her to a local hospital. The friend called police and they arrived at the home, in central Jeffrey&rsquo;s Bay, at 12:00 on Thursday.&nbsp;Swart said on Friday that police were still taking statements. A post-mortem would be conducted to establish the cause of the girl&rsquo;s death.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.